<!-- wp:proposal-crafter/paragraph {"uniqueId":"22751cf","css":".pc22751cf{border-style:none;border-color:#000000;border-width:0px 0px 0px 0px;margin:0px 0px 110px 0px !important;}.pc22751cf__overlay{padding:0px 0px 0px 0px !important;}.pc22751cf .pc-paragraph{text-align:left;color:#707070;font-size:12px;font-family:DM Sans;font-weight:400;}","content":"\u003cbr\u003eAny fonts/typefaces that are purchased for the final logo, and/or supporting brand identity assets, are subject to commercial licensing laws. A font/typeface licences gives the only the owner full rights to use the font/typeface as necessary.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf during the project I feel that a commercial font/typeface is appropriate for the development of your logo and brand identity, I will convey this to you at that time, and a licence, if you agree, must be purchased/ and/or registered to you before the project is finalised.\u003cbr\u003eIt is against the law for me to provide any client a ‘copy’ of any font/typeface that I own, and have personally purchased.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf you would like to use a copy of a font/typeface that I have purchased, to be used commercially, you must purchase the respective font/typeface licence, and register it in your name. If you wish me to facilitate the purchase and registering of any font on your behalf, I’d be more than happy to do so, and will add the cost to the final invoice.","fontSize":12,"fontFamily":"DM Sans","color":"#707070","margin":{"top":"0px","right":"0px","bottom":"110px","left":"0px"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-proposal-crafter-paragraph pc22751cf" data-block-id="22751cf"><div class="pc22751cf__overlay"><p class="pc-paragraph"><br>Any fonts/typefaces that are purchased for the final logo, and/or supporting brand identity assets, are subject to commercial licensing laws. A font/typeface licences gives the only the owner full rights to use the font/typeface as necessary.<br><br>If during the project I feel that a commercial font/typeface is appropriate for the development of your logo and brand identity, I will convey this to you at that time, and a licence, if you agree, must be purchased/ and/or registered to you before the project is finalised.<br>It is against the law for me to provide any client a ‘copy’ of any font/typeface that I own, and have personally purchased.<br><br>If you would like to use a copy of a font/typeface that I have purchased, to be used commercially, you must purchase the respective font/typeface licence, and register it in your name. If you wish me to facilitate the purchase and registering of any font on your behalf, I’d be more than happy to do so, and will add the cost to the final invoice.</p></div></div>
<!-- /wp:proposal-crafter/paragraph -->

